article.headline: Wright St. 87, Md.-Eastern Shore 46
article.story: DAYTON, Ohio -- Todd Brown scored 16 points and Cooper Land added 14 off the bench as Wright State routed Maryland-Eastern Shore 87-46 on Saturday night. After trailing 9-7, the Raiders (7-4) blew past the Hawks (3-6) with a 35-11 spurt over the final 13:14 of the first half for a 42-20 lead. Land scored eight points in that stretch, including two 3-pointers. Wright State widened the gap to 56-20 by starting the second half with a 14-0 run that included seven turnovers by Maryland-Eastern Shore. The Hawks committed 20 turnovers in the game to the Raiders' seven. Wright State also outshot Maryland-Eastern Shore 54.2 percent (32-for-59) to 36.4 percent (16-for-44) and got 44 points off its bench to nine for Maryland-Eastern Shore. Kevin White scored 16 points, 11 of them in the first half, to lead Maryland-Eastern Shore. Scott Grote added 11 points and six assists for Wright State.
